post: {'type': 'con', 'text': "Several 'great' artists have died from an overdose on drugs and thus actually causing negative contributions to human culture as the world is deprived of their 'artwork'."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "It may be difficult to find and employ the right kind of medical professionals who can support the user's needs effectively \\(helping the user in dealing with trauma from their past & their conditioning from childhood\\) I think drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Since drug addicts have an impaired sense of \\(rational\\) judgement, drug addiction is detrimental to personal autonomy.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Heroin and other opiates cause [negligible](https://rationalwiki.org/wiki/Heroin#Health_effects) direct physical harm to the body. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "An Indian based study shows that substance consumption highly relate to [juvenile delinquency.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4919962/) That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Taking the stigma and secrecy away from drug taking would mean family and friends would notice drug abuse earlier and be able to intervene.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If government regulations lead to drugs being expensive, it is possible people will still try to access cheaper drugs on a black market and these drugs may still be dangerous or of poor quality. I think legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is no way to determine in advance what the additional resources/revenue will be used for by the government. It may not be earmarked for harm reduction. So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Allowing people to become addicted merely so we can understand addiction is socially and medically irresponsible. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'They would have died on those drugs whether or not they were legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Currently, in the USA, there is a [pharmaceutical opioid crisis](https://www.cfr.org/backgrounder/us-opioid-epidemic). Drug companies and legal policies cannot be trusted to protect citizens. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the Andes, [coca](https://nacla.org/article/beat-goes-us-war-coca), a sacred plant harmful when mass produced as a cash crop, has replaced the production of fruits and vegetables.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalization of recreational drug use is not necessary for legalization of expanded drug research. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The first [anti-opium laws](http://www.drugpolicy.org/issues/brief-history-drug-war) in the 1870s were directed at Chinese immigrants. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "In a truly free society self regulation should be our privilege. You are free to not use drugs, and you should be just as free to use them. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalisation of drugs allows for them to be regulated by the state and sold directly to the consumer, increasing purity. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The prosecution takes place after the repercussions have occurred. A ban can prevent them from ever happening.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Making things safer is always preferable.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'During prohibition, there were very few production standards \\(if any\\), meaning the consumer did not know what \\(potentially dangerous\\) conditions the alcohol had been manufactured in \\([pg. 4](https://object.cato.org/pubs/pas/pa157.pdf)\\).'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This does not take into account plants that do not grow well everywhere. For these cases, there is still a reliance on other communities that fall under different legislation to cultivate the plants. This keeps a connection with the international criminal drug trade.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The war on drugs has [cost civilian lives](https://www.vox.com/2014/10/29/7083371/swat-no-knock-raids-police-killed-civilians-dangerous-work-drugs). That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is a tautological argument, presupposing that prohibiting drugs is morally right.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The anxiety induced by the threat of arrest can be a cause for the violent paranoia episodes some users experience while under the influence emotion enhancing substances.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[High individuals](https://philosophynow.org/issues/113/On_Moral_Arguments_Against_Recreational_Drug_Use) know the difference between right and wrong and can understand when they are hurting others.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A large portion of the public is irresponsible. Giving everyone the opportunity to use \\(or abuse\\) drugs would have negative consequences on these individuals.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The cigarette industry suppressed research that demonstrated the carcinogenicity of cigarettes \\([pg. 2](https://www.who.int/tobacco/media/en/TobaccoExplained.pdf)\\).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many users currently do not properly dispose of their paraphernalia for fear of being caught with it on them, leading to evidence of illegal drug use being disposed of quickly and carelessly.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs such as PCP have caused [grotesque instances](https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/real-life-stories/rapper-killed-girlfriend-chewed-up-11566075) of violence by the user onto other individuals.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Drugs relate highly with](https://www.ojjdp.gov/pubs/coachesplaybook/effects_of_using.html) hampered physical and professional performance.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[A study](http://aic.gov.au/media_library/publications/tandi_pdf/tandi372.pdf) came to the conclusion that alcohol consumption was involved in 47% of homicides in Australia in a six-year period. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalisation of drugs allows for them to be regulated by the state and sold directly to the consumer, increasing purity. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Having drugs be both illegal and valuable has funded extensive infrastructure for smuggling things across the US border.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Making things safer is always preferable.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help drive down the profits of drug cartels since people could get their drugs from legal reliable sources. Hence it may force the cartels to offer a purer product or less expensive to remain competitive. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Cocaine, a commonly-used illegal drug, has [multiple negative health effects](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cocaine_intoxication) on the user.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Other factors contribute to the opioid crisis significantly more than the legality of currently prescribed opioids. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The same applies to already legal alcohol. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue is not drug legalization, but the functioning of the health insurances. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Making it legal for companies to sell and market these drugs for recreational use without an understanding of the negative consequences that these substances cause is unethical. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Numerous events have an equal impact on moral judgments; This should not be the reason for the ban on drug use. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use negatively affects job performance.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the same way that people sign contracts in which they voluntarily limit their freedom for a certain amount of time, a person who chooses freely to take drugs is choosing to limit their self-control freely. In either case, the initial choice is still a free choice. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Creativity can be stimulated through the use of drugs. Drugs could help us to live in a more creative dynamic society.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since these would most likely be legally bought products, it would be much easier for the authorities have control over it, as opposed to illegally produced and smuggled goods.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs can be used to abuse others or commit crimes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Recreational drugs can be used as self medication especially for those with severe mental health issues like PTSD and psychosis.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs are insanely profitable at a relatively low level of effort, as opposed to other crimes.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "This is perhaps a fantastic way to prevent drug abuse in children and, hopefully therefore, adults too. However, it doesn't contribute to bringing down cartels or allow healthy adults to use recreational drugs in the safest possible way."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While neither seems acceptable, most would rather face prejudice than prison. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "This is an argument of the ends justifying the means. The government could generate more income by simply taking everyone's money by force - that doesn't make it a good choice. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs will help treat addicts. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If someone is willing to commit an act as vile as date raping someone, they're probably not going to care very much about whether they have to purchase the drug illegally."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It may be very difficult to diagnose which individuals suffer from self-inflicted mental illness or trauma and which ones are taking drugs as a result of their condition.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the long run, the standing of the U.S. government did not suffer from ending the Alcohol Prohibition in the 1930s. Any potential reputational damage from ending marijuana or other prohibitions would be fleeting.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If someone is willing to commit an act as vile as date raping someone, they're probably not going to care very much about whether they have to purchase the drug illegally."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Other factors contribute to the opioid crisis significantly more than the legality of currently prescribed opioids. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Personal autonomy](https://www.law.cornell.edu/wex/personal_autonomy) is not a fundamental right in the US constitution.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If these substances legitimately are so dangerous, they _should_ primarily be considered weapons and not drugs. They can then be ignored in this discussion. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The illegal trade is already there. The legal trade would just drain their customer base. For criminal trade to survive in those conditions it would have to have either cheaper prices or better product. These are not easily achieved agains big corporations. At least the competition would seriously damage their overheads.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Patients will be able to create, combine or grow their own medicines.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help law enforcement agencies.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Illegality over the last century has halted research on the many new psychoactive substances that have been discovered in that time \\(as well as traditional ones\\).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, addicts would be forced to buy legally, meaning there is a record of their usage and authorities can intervene if there is an instance of drug abuse.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Without the effect of the forbidden fruit, drugs would not be 'cool' anymore \\(subcultures, arts, musicians, writers, etc.\\). Removing this effect would minimize the number of people who use drugs because they feel insecure or want to belong in a group."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Creativity can be stimulated through the use of drugs. Drugs could help us to live in a more creative dynamic society.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Science can already study drugs, just with some [constraints](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4307971/). I think legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Tracing the rapist after the rape does not undo the rape itself, as the harm was already done.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the US, as of 2018 there are roughly [235,000](https://www.prisonpolicy.org/reports/pie2018.html) inmates behind bars for drug-related crimes. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Aquiring drugs in a legal setting allows for regulation that may require informing the buyer about dangerous combinations, or avoid selling to people already under the influence of other drugs. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Suicide rates may increase as overdose will be an easily accessible option.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Sensible legal drug policy would uses taxes to keep prices equal or slightly below current black market prices to keep that from occuring. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs may also alter the strength of which learning \\(permanent changes of neural activity\\) reacts to such rewards.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Decriminalization would encourage the implementation of a broader scope of impairment detection devices. This would cause users to think twice about driving impaired on substances they believe wouldn't be detected using current methods. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Regulations that prohibit working under the influence of alcohol can trivially be expanded to include all drugs. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The right to bodily integrity protects individuals from [forced labor, slavery or torture](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bodily_integrity).'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs may be adulterated despite legalisation, like [alcoholic beverages.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20959682) I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug use is not the same as drug addiction.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In 2018, the consumption patterns of most US citizens who used illicit drugs were [unproblematic](https://filtermag.org/2018/09/25/the-invisible-majority-people-whose-drug-use-is-not-problematic/). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The evidence provided in this claim stems largely from importing cheaper cigarettes from the rest of Europe to the UK. The difference in quality is probably minimal. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The banning of alcohol [significantly increased the ability of organized crime to make money](http://prohibition.themobmuseum.org/the-history/the-rise-of-organized-crime/the-mob-during-prohibition/). That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The human body is very complex; a given drug can have quite subtle aspects. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Without the effect of the forbidden fruit, drugs would not be 'cool' anymore \\(subcultures, arts, musicians, writers, etc.\\). Removing this effect would minimize the number of people who use drugs because they feel insecure or want to belong in a group."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This ignores proportionality \\(meaning how many people were negatively affected and to what magnitude\\).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs has criminalized a large number of otherwise innocent individuals.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "It's always going to be cheaper to produce a product legally. Legal producers don't have to worry about having their stuff stolen by police and can do all their transactions in the legal market which is much more efficient and cheaper."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug use will not cease regardless of the legal status. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug legalisation would mean governments get to suggest a recommended dose, preventing the incidence of death by overdose. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Having the option to buy regulated drugs is surely better than only having the black market option. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Through education, heavy advertising campaigns and controlling the packaging of tobacco, the government can make its negative effects clear despite it being legal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Albert Hofman](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Albert_Hofmann), the creator of LSD, took LSD for over two decades without any health implications.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Governments invested a lot of money trying to cease drug use by everyone. It failed miserably. Not only it is not the most efficient way, but it is not even achievable.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Constitutions can be amended by the Federal Government to suit their policies.'}
